==English==
===Etymology===
Etymology said to come from [[Hebrew]] via [[Yiddish]] and into [[English]] phrases, originally from ''hakol b’seder'', “all is in order”, or ''kol b’tzedek'', “all's with justice”.

===Adjective===
'''copacetic'''

#Fine, excellent, going just right, [[swell]].

